

## Overview
This room focuses on Windows forensic investigation techniques including event logs, scheduled tasks, processes, and network activity to identify malicious behavior.

## Key Learning Areas
- Windows Event Logs analysis
- User logon tracking
- Scheduled Tasks investigation
- Persistence mechanisms
- Process & service analysis
- Network connections monitoring

## Windows Event Logs Location
Windows event logs are stored in:

C:\Windows\System32\winevt\Logs\

## Important Event IDs

| Event ID | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| 4624 | Successful logon |
| 4625 | Failed logon |
| 4634 | Logoff |
| 4672 | Special privileges assigned |
| 4688 | New process created |
| 4698 | Scheduled task created |
| 4719 | Audit policy changed |

